<p>Question - One hiccup we had when trying out the “kResetSafeParameters” versus “kNoResetSafeParameters” was after we bypassed the limit switch was that the Flex continued to flash white/green at us indicating the Flex believes the hard limit was still reached and would not reset. Will the “Async” prevent the limit switch from auto resetting? Or will the true/false cases reset the limit switch upon pressing the buttons?</p>
<p>Note - I really do appreciate everyone’s help on this!</p>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":11,"updated_at":"2025-02-03T18:21:55.767Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":8,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":41,"readers_count":40,"score":18.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":484278,"topic_slug":"disable-limit-switch-on-rev-spark-flex","display_username":"burde1jb","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":17898,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"FRC Team 4327"},"post_url":"/t/disable-limit-switch-on-rev-spark-flex/484278/9","custom_user_title":"FRC Team 4327","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3500988,"name":"Dan","username":"tekdemo","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/tekdemo/{size}/138330_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-03T20:19:43.007Z","cooked":"<p>kResetSafeParameters doesn’t impact the limit switch in that way. Those clear all <em>other</em> settings beyond the currently selected config (such as conversion factors, current limits, and <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> tunings), and is almost certainly not something you want to send mid-match.</p>
<p>The Spark itself will not retain memory of the switch being pressed once it’s unpressed*.</p>
<p>One scenario that may be at play is simply the switch wiring. Electrically, the Spark must be able to restore the wire voltage back to the “before-pressed” state. Depending on what switch you have and how the switch is wired, it may not be able to do that. Photos or diagrams of how it’s wired might help.</p>
<p>The typical way to wire these is as shown here, pulling the GND and 3.3V from the Rev data port.<br>
<img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/9/c/9cbc1a3591b2c39c338ecb1f1635f38ed08b3307.jpeg" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="mmxuyDbtyY2WC8hVY2IoQViqb6T" width="571" height="389"><br>
