<p>The other way to wire them is using a “pull up resistor”. This is functionally identical to the above, but you don’t need a 3.3V wire (leaving that terminal empty). In such a case, the microcontroller is responsible<br>
This is great in most cases, but in <span class="abbreviation">FRC<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="FIRST Robotics Competition"></template></span> specifically, I’d suggest connecting all 3 wires to your switch, as it provides better signal clarity and avoids some issues.</p>
